<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Many questions for expert players</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?blarg">blarg</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:19 a.m. 22/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Many questions for expert players<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Ok i have been playing eq for a while now, but it seems the # of questions increase as I gain lvls and expand my knoweledge of the world

<BR>1. Items with 1 charge, such as Spring and Harvest crystals, eventually loose the abily to summon food and drink. Can they be recharge (paid about 6pp for each)
<BR>2. I heard a rumor that most good magic armour (chain/platemail) is only medium size only, thus smaller races and larger races dont get to wear best armour in the game?
<BR>3. I have found a book of an named npc orc/goblin (cant recall). I been offered up to 40pp for it. I heard there is a way to research new spells from it. Is it true? if yes are these spells unique to mage class only or can hybrid classes also learn it and how do I research these spells. also are these spells different from what npc sell?
<BR>4. Last question (and rather silly one) Why does iron ration cost 10 times more than normal ration, they seem to last about the same time. Is it the neutrition value? :)
<BR>Thanks for your help
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
